    "name": "Kenny Håkansson (2)",
    "profile": "Swedish guitarist, born November 12, 1945 in Stockholm.\r\n\r\nWhen Kenny was 15 years old, he intended to buy a trombone for money he earned on a summer job. The music store also had electric guitars, so instead of a trombone he ended up buying a Höfner guitar. This was in -59 or -60. He went through a number of bands:\r\n\r\n1: The Agents, own band with brother and friends, ca -63\r\n2: T-Boones: joined in about -65\r\n3: Baby Grandmothers: own band together with Pelle Ekman and Bella Ferlin. -67\r\n4. Mecki Mark Men, merger of BGm and MMM. -68\r\n5: Kebnekajse, together with Pelle E., Bella F., and Roffe Scherrer. Summer -71\r\n6: Dag Vag, joined in -79\r\n7: Bill's Boogie Band, formed together with Bill öhrström, Jukka Tolonen, Hasse Larsson and Bosse Skoglund. -84\r\n\r\nBeside the bands, he played with Cornelis, Lisa Ekdahl, Janne Hammarlund, Clas-Göran Hedenström, Jack Downing and more.",
